__init__(string,string).details: Initialises the domain separator and the parameter caches. To omit the opcodes for checking the `msg.value` in the creation-time EVM bytecode, the constructor is declared as `payable`.

params.name_: The maximum 50-character user-readable string name of the signing domain, i.e. the name of the dApp or protocol.
params.version_: The maximum 20-character current main version of the signing domain. Signatures from different versions are not compatible.

domain_separator_v4().details: Returns the domain separator for the current chain.

eip712Domain().details: Returns the fields and values that describe the domain separator used by this contract for EIP-712 signatures.

returns._0: bytes1 The 1-byte bit map where bit `i` is set to 1 if and only if domain field `i` is present (`0 ≤ i ≤ 4`).
returns._1: String The maximum 50-character user-readable string name of the signing domain, i.e. the name of the dApp or protocol.
returns._2: String The maximum 20-character current main version of the signing domain. Signatures from different versions are not compatible.
returns._4: address The 20-byte address of the verifying contract.
returns._5: bytes32 The 32-byte disambiguation salt for the protocol.
returns._6: DynArray The 32-byte array of EIP-712 extensions.

hash_typed_data_v4(bytes32).details: Returns the hash of the fully encoded EIP-712 message for this domain.

returns._0: bytes32 The 32-byte fully encoded EIP712 message hash for this domain.

devdoc.title: EIP-712 Domain Separator

__init__(string,string).notice: The definition of the domain separator can be found here: https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-712#definition-of-domainseparator. Since the Vyper design requires strings of fixed size, we arbitrarily set the maximum length for `name` to 50 characters and `version` to 20 characters.

eip712Domain().notice: The bits in the 1-byte bit map are read from the least significant to the most significant, and fields are indexed in the order that is specified by EIP-712, identical to the order in which they are listed in the function type.

hash_typed_data_v4(bytes32).notice: The definition of the hashed struct can be found here: https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-712#definition-of-hashstruct.

userdoc.notice: These functions are part of EIP-712: https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-712. These functions implement the version of encoding known as "v4" as implemented by the JSON-RPC method: https://docs.metamask.io/guide/signing-data.html#sign-typed-data-v4. In addition, this contract also implements EIP-5267: https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-5267. The implementation is inspired by OpenZeppelin's implementation here: https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/master/contracts/utils/cryptography/EIP712.sol.
